To show you what I mean, I spoke yesterday to John Major and John Smith. It really is a spectacle. But in private they relax. You are the most unpopular prime minister since the start of the fourth century. In reality, all politicians, not just Major, are far more candid and salty when chatting in private than when speaking in public. Their responses were true to form. They swear and joke and shout. No one could have eavesdropped. To guarantee them privacy, I used a signal-scrambler. What do you say to that.  like, Christchurch, y'know - load of . 